Wash and dry produce. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if
necessary. Trim and slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.
Quarter @lime{1}.

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot #stainless steel pan{}. Add
@chicken breast strips{10%ounce} in a single layer; season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Lower heat under pan; stir in @sweet soy glaze{8%tbsp} and @water{2%tbsp}
(4 TBSP for 4). Cook until sauce is slightly thickened and chicken is
evenly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

While chicken cooks, in a #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine broccoli,
scallion whites, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and @water{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4).
Cover with #plastic wrap{}; poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until tender,
~{1-2%minutes}. Drain.
> No microwave? No problem! Boil broccoli in a pot of salted water until tender,
 ~{2-4%minutes}. Drain.

Toss broccoli with as many @Korean chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. Season with
@salt{}.

Massage @microwavable rice{1} package; snip to partially open. Microwave for
~{90%seconds}. Carefully open package; mix in @cashews{1%ounce},
@butter{1%tbsp}, juice from one lime wedge, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}
(2 TBSP butter and juice from two wedges for 4).

In a second #bowl{}, mix @mayonnaise{2%tbsp},
@sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and juice from one lime wedge (juice from
two wedges for 4).

Top rice with saucy chicken and broccoli in separate sections. Drizzle
everything with spicy mayo. Top with scallion greens and
@crispy fried onions{1}. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.